<br>
So, with my new understanding, when I am playing my melee alts, I make sure every other vendor trash item I loot goes to my casters, healer first, then the others, cause they are there to help me out and I need to show my appreciation of that (this is mostly for lower levels, obviously, I have not been to the good loot places yet).<br>
<br>
The way to apply this to the higher levels, I guess, would be to either make sure your healers get at least one good item they can either use or sell (peridots are expensive, and so are spells, and casters need equip upgrades too), or make sure you bring the cleric a stack of dots for them to use while casting symbol on you. Either way, make sure you take care of your healer, cause we also take names, and clerics have little trouble finding groups these days <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Mahrriah Windrider 49th season Druid<br>
